}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{1\'2e Consumer vs\'2e customer, consumer behaviour, models of consumer 
behavior\line
2\'2e Customer in this time and in future, his life style\line
3\'2e marketing and psychology access to typology of consumers\line
4\'2e Typology of customers according to research agency GfK, AISA, 
communications \line
   agency Young & Rubicam and TN Sofres\line
5\'2e Market research as part of information system retailing company, 
sorts of \line
   research, source of informations\'2e Respondents for typy market 
research, \line
   selections of respondents\line
6\'2e Aplication of kvantitive market research in retailing company\line
7\'2e Aplication of kvalitative market research in retailing company\line
8\'2e Mark vs\'2e Brand (substance, diferences, importance for retailing 
company\line
   strategic managing of brand\'2e Aplication private labels of retailing 
chains\line
9\'2e Marketing and commercial communications in retailing company, 
substance, \line
   form, characteristics, importance\line
10\'2e\'46orms of ATL a BTL marketing communications activities (In\_Store, 
Sales \line
   Promotion, Sampling, Merchandising, Couponing, Event Marketin g 
and their \line
   aplication in retailing company\line
11\'2eCRM (Consumer Relationship Management)and its aplication in 
